# deploy.config — local settings for scripts/deploy.sh AND scripts/deploy.ps1
#
#   cp deploy.config.example deploy.config     # then fill in your values
#   (PowerShell: Copy-Item deploy.config.example deploy.config)
#
# deploy.config is git-ignored, so hostnames and paths stay on your machine.
# Only fill in the section for the target you use; leave the rest commented.
# Keep it to simple KEY="value" lines — the PowerShell script parses the same
# file, so shell-only syntax ($HOME, $(…), multi-line values) won't work.

# ── Target: ssh (your own webserver — nginx, Apache, Caddy…) ──────────────
# The server just needs to serve static files; the docroot must be reachable
# over SSH. Example result: https://cv.example.com served from /var/www/cv
#DEPLOY_SSH_HOST="cv.example.com"
#DEPLOY_SSH_USER="deploy"
#DEPLOY_SSH_PORT="22"
#DEPLOY_SSH_PATH="/var/www/cv"

# ── Target: cloudflare (Cloudflare Pages) ─────────────────────────────────
# Optional — with it set, deploys run without the interactive project prompt.
#CF_PAGES_PROJECT="webcv"

# ── Target: gh-pages (GitHub Pages) ───────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub Pages only works for this app when served at a DOMAIN ROOT (see
# README — the 3D model URLs are root-absolute). Two supported setups:
#   1. Custom domain: set GHPAGES_CNAME and point your DNS at GitHub Pages.
#   2. A <user>.github.io root repository: set GHPAGES_ROOT_OK=1 instead.
#GHPAGES_CNAME="cv.example.com"
#GHPAGES_ROOT_OK=1
#GHPAGES_REMOTE="origin"
#GHPAGES_BRANCH="gh-pages"

# ── Target: netlify / vercel ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# No variables needed here — both CLIs store their link/auth state themselves
# (run the one-time login/init commands shown in scripts/deploy.sh|.ps1).
# For CI / non-interactive Netlify deploys you can export instead:
#   NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=…   NETLIFY_SITE_ID=…
